			"after": " Upon leaving the country Emperor Pedro I selected three people to take charge of his son and remaining daughters The first was Jos Bonif cio de Andrada his friend and an influential leader during Brazilian independence who was named guardian 19 20 The second was Mariana de Verna who had held the post of aia governess since the birth of Pedro II 21 As a child the then Prince Imperial called her Dadama as he could not pronounce the word dama Lady correctly 11 He regarded her as his surrogate mother and would continue to call her by her nickname well into adulthood out of affection 18 22 The third person was Rafael an Afro Brazilian veteran of the Cisplatine War 21 23 He was an employee in the Palace of S o Crist v o whom Pedro I deeply trusted and asked to look after his son a charge that he carried out for the rest of his life 10 23 ",
